+
+- Forty-sixth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S4-P02). After the Owner S4 cohort gate approved SCALE for the A0-WAVE-1 cohort, executed the first real A0 2016+ history backfill Wave. release_mode SHADOW. The backfill ran from the dev environment against the real gov.cn policy library: it discovered 7 real policy content URLs across 6 distinct months and parsed each through the T034 gov.cn adapter, then ran them through the T021/T022 content-addressed raw-key idempotency, the T026 append-only version chain, and the T027 month partitioning. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S4-P02-T046/: wave1_backfill_docs.json, backfill_manifest.json, and gap_cost_report.json. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S4-P02-T046/test-results/backfill_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): 7 real A0 policy originals were backfilled across 6 distinct months from 2019-04 to 2022-01, all at or after 2016-01; realtime was not regressed, since the Wave ran from the dev environment with no worker deploy, so the live build stayed b189d3cc0703 (equal to T040), the six themes stayed 6/6, and today returned 200; the backfill is idempotent, since re-running the identical batch adds 0 new content-addressed objects and no duplicates; the version chain produced 7 versions for the 7 canonical documents; attachments were preserved; and the month coverage is 6 distinct months. It carried 0 cloud cost because it executed from the dev environment (about 8 dev-env subrequests, not the worker), so DIR-007 is unaffected; the literal full 2016+ coverage accrues over real calendar time once the adapters are wired to the worker cron under the T042 backfill lane and the DIR-007 cap. Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S4-P02-T045 (A0 backfill cohort selection by user value; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Forty-fifth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S4-P02 (A0 2016+ history cohort). Goal: cover the high-value central and national-level domains first instead of blindly opening every source in Registry order. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; a cohort selection proposal, not an execution -- the actual backfill is T046 and is gated by the Owner S4 cohort decision (SCALE / HOLD / STOP). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/cohort_selector.py (a value_score of 0.4 times domain value plus 0.3 times coverage gap plus 0.3 times stability, a stop_rule, and select_cohort that orders by descending value and gives every member an authority role, a history start, expected document types, a stop rule, and the expected benefit while deferring a live-blocked source), COHORT_SELECTOR_SPEC.md, and evidence/ADP-S4-P02-T045/cohort_manifest.json. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S4-P02-T045/test-results/cohort_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the Wave-1 cohort has 5 members ordered by user value rather than Registry order -- gov-cn-policy at 1.0, gov-cn-fagui at 0.965, stats-gov at 0.9, cac-gov at 0.88, and ndrc-gov at 0.865 -- every member carries an authority role, a history start, expected document types, a stop rule, and an expected benefit; and the live-blocked nda-gov is deferred with a reason rather than blindly opened. The Wave-1 cohort is proposed for the Owner S4 cohort gate before T046 executes it. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
